original: Johansson, Oskar William Eugen, apotekare, Borås, f. 20/2/88 i Vårgår-da, Älvsb. 1., av Carl J. o. Maria Ähman. G. 15 m. Emy Andersson. — Studiex. i Gbg 08, res:off:ex. 10, farm. kand. 12, apot:ex. 20. Und:-löjtn. i Bohusl. reg. res. 10, löjtn. 15, avsk. 22. Elev v. apot. Lejonet i Gbg 09-11, anst. v. apot. S:t Erik i Sthlm 12-14, Morianen där 18-20, Avesta 20-24, Lejonet i Jönköp. 24-29, Kronan i Borås 29-37, priv. å apot. i Sunnan-sjö 37-43, priv. å apot. Storken i Borås sed. 43. V. ordf. i Viästg :krets. av Sv. iapot :förb. 46, ordf. sed. 47.
translated: Johansson, Oskar William Eugen, pharmacist, Borås, born February 20, 1888 in Vårgårda, Älvsborgs län, son of Carl J. and Maria Ähman. Married in 1915 to Emy Andersson. Completed his studies in Gothenburg in 1908, military officer training in 1910, pharmaceutical degree in 1912, and pharmacy license in 1920. He was a second lieutenant in the Bohuslän regiment in 1910, promoted to lieutenant in 1915, and retired in 1922. He was a student at the Lejonet pharmacy in Gothenburg from 1909-1911. He was employed at the S:t Erik pharmacy in Stockholm from 1912-1914, then at Morianen from 1918-1920, at Avesta from 1920-1924, at Lejonet in Jönköping from 1924-1929, and at Kronan in Borås from 1929-1937. He was a private pharmacist at the Sunnansjö pharmacy from 1937-1943, and at the Storken pharmacy in Borås from 1943 onward. He was the vice chairman of the Västergötland region of the Swedish Pharmacy Association in 1946, and has been the chairman since 1947.
